**Data flow — Phase 1 (Adversarial Debate):** User submits task via React UI → WebSocket → FastAPI. DA generates ExecutionPlan as structured JSON: list of SubTask objects (task_id, description, agent_type, tools_needed, output_schema, depends_on) plus a dependency graph and token estimate. EA receives plan, returns EACritique: gaps[], edge_cases[], redundancies[], improvements[], sub_scores {completeness: float, coherence: float, efficiency: float, dependency_correctness: float}, confidence (weighted average), approved (bool). DA revises incorporating critique. Loop until confidence ≥ 0.8 or 3 rounds. EA confidence is computed as: (completeness × 0.3) + (coherence × 0.3) + (efficiency × 0.2) + (dependency_correctness × 0.2).

**Data flow — Phase 2 (Dynamic Execution):** Approved ExecutionPlan enters the prompt generation pipeline. Each SubTask produces an AgentConfig via generate_agent_config(). Independent tasks (empty depends_on) launch in parallel via asyncio.gather(). Dependent tasks wait for prerequisites. MMA pre-loads filtered context from predecessor outputs using dependency-graph routing and schema-aware extraction. Each sub-agent writes AgentOutput to MMA store.

**Data flow — Phase 3 (Assembly):** DA collects outputs from MMA ordered by dependency graph. DA synthesizes coherent response. EA performs final quality review. Result streamed to user via WebSocket with full provenance.

**Core data models:**

```python
class NexusState(TypedDict):
    user_request: str
    debate_history: list[DebateRound]
    approved_plan: ExecutionPlan | None
    sub_tasks: list[SubTask]
    sub_agent_outputs: dict[str, AgentOutput]
    final_output: str | None
    phase: Literal["debate", "execute", "assemble", "complete"]

class DebateRound(TypedDict):
    round_number: int
    da_proposal: str
    ea_critique: EACritique
    confidence: float

class EACritique(TypedDict):
    gaps: list[str]
    edge_cases: list[str]
    redundancies: list[str]
    improvements: list[str]
    sub_scores: dict[str, float]  # completeness, coherence, efficiency, dependency_correctness
    confidence: float             # weighted: comp*0.3 + coh*0.3 + eff*0.2 + dep*0.2
    approved: bool

class ExecutionPlan(TypedDict):
    tasks: list[SubTask]
    dependencies: dict[str, list[str]]
    estimated_tokens: int

class SubTask(TypedDict):
    task_id: str
    description: str
    agent_type: str           # Key into AGENT_TEMPLATES registry
    tools_needed: list[str]   # Key into TOOL_REGISTRY
    output_schema: dict       # Injected into prompt AND used by MMA for schema-aware extraction
    depends_on: list[str]     # Task IDs — MMA uses for dependency-graph routing

class AgentOutput(TypedDict):
    task_id: str
    status: Literal["success", "partial", "failed"]
    result: Any
    metadata: dict            # tokens_used, execution_time_ms
```

